import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['distance'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Distances')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of distances between airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    ax = state_counts.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(12, 6), color='c')
    ax.set_title('Which state has the highest number of airports?')
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Airports')
    ax.axhline(state_counts.max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {state_counts.max():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['latitude'], data['longitude'])
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Longitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude of airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    names = data['name'].values
    text = ' '.join(names)
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', colormap='viridis').generate(text)

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    country_counts = data['country'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(country_counts, labels=country_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by country?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title="Countries", loc="best")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
